HEADWORD: Bloomery
<hw>Bloom"er*y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Manuf.)</fld>
<def>A furnace and forge in which wrought iron in the form of blooms is
made directly from the ore, or (more rarely) from cast iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blooming</ent>⟦br⟧
